---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Getting Started with the Boilerplate">
  <main id="main-content" class="page-main">
    <div class="page-inner">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/getting-started/">Getting Started</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
        <span>Boilerplate</span>
      </nav>

      <h1>Getting Started with the Boilerplate</h1>
      <div class="page-content">
        <p class="lead">
          The fastest way to start a FuryStack project. Clone a ready-made template with
          authentication, REST API, and a Shades frontend &mdash; all wired up.
        </p>

        <p>
          The <a
            href="https://github.com/furystack/boilerplate"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Boilerplate repository</a
          >
          is a GitHub template you can use to create your own repo in seconds. It is a
          <a
            href="https://yarnpkg.com/features/workspaces"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Yarn workspaces</a
          >
          monorepo with three packages: <strong>common</strong>, <strong>service</strong>, and <strong
            >frontend</strong
          >.
        </p>

        <h2>Quick start</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>
            Open the <a
              href="https://github.com/furystack/boilerplate"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer">boilerplate repo</a
            >
            and click <strong>Use this template</strong> to create your own repository.
          </li>
          <li>
            Clone your new repo and install dependencies:
            <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/your-user/your-repo.git
cd your-repo
yarn install</code></pre>
          </li>
          <li>
            Build all workspaces:
            <pre><code>yarn build</code></pre>
          </li>
          <li>
            Start the backend and frontend (in separate terminals):
            <pre><code>yarn start:service
yarn start:frontend</code></pre>
          </li>
          <li>
            Open <a href="http://localhost:8080/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >http://localhost:8080/</a
            > in your browser.
          </li>
        </ol>

        <hr />

        <h2>Project structure</h2>
        <p>
          The monorepo is managed with <strong>Yarn 4</strong> workspaces. Every package uses ESM (<code
            >"type": "module"</code
          >) and TypeScript with project references (<code>tsc&nbsp;-b</code>).
        </p>

        <h3>common</h3>
        <p>
          Shared models and type-safe REST API definitions. Both the service and the frontend depend
          on this package via <code>"common": "workspace:^"</code>.
        </p>
        <p>
          The API contract is defined as a TypeScript interface that extends <code>RestApi</code>
          from <code>@furystack/rest</code>:
        </p>
        <pre><code>import type &#123; RestApi &#125; from '@furystack/rest'
import type &#123; User &#125; from './models/index.js'

export interface BoilerplateApi extends RestApi &#123;
  GET: &#123;
    '/isAuthenticated': &#123; result: &#123; isAuthenticated: boolean &#125; &#125;
    '/currentUser': &#123; result: User &#125;
    '/testQuery': &#123; query: &#123; param1: string &#125;; result: &#123; param1Value: string &#125; &#125;
  &#125;
  POST: &#123;
    '/login': &#123; result: User; body: &#123; username: string; password: string &#125; &#125;
    '/logout': &#123; result: unknown &#125;
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>
        <p>
          This single interface drives both the server routing and the client&rsquo;s typed fetch
          calls, giving you end-to-end type safety.
        </p>

        <h3>service</h3>
        <p>The Node.js backend, built entirely on FuryStack packages:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <code>@furystack/core</code> &mdash; <code>InMemoryStore</code>, <code>addStore</code>
          </li>
          <li>
            <code>@furystack/inject</code> &mdash; dependency injection via <code>Injector</code>
          </li>
          <li><code>@furystack/repository</code> &mdash; data sets with authorization hooks</li>
          <li>
            <code>@furystack/rest-service</code> &mdash; <code>useRestService</code> to spin up an HTTP
            server from the API type
          </li>
          <li><code>@furystack/auth-jwt</code> &mdash; JWT login / logout / refresh</li>
          <li><code>@furystack/security</code> &mdash; password hashing and policies</li>
          <li><code>@furystack/filesystem-store</code> &mdash; persist entities to JSON files</li>
          <li><code>@furystack/logging</code> &mdash; structured logging</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The entry point wires everything together:</p>
        <pre><code>import &#123; injector &#125; from './root-injector.js'
import &#123; attachShutdownHandler &#125; from './shutdown-handler.js'
import &#123; setupStore &#125; from './setup-store.js'
import &#123; setupRestApi &#125; from './setup-rest-api.js'

void attachShutdownHandler(injector)
setupStore(injector)

setupRestApi(injector).catch((err) =&gt; &#123;
  console.error(err)
  process.exit(1)
&#125;)</code></pre>

        <h3>frontend</h3>
        <p>
          A single-page app built with
          <a
            href="https://github.com/furystack/furystack/tree/develop/packages/shades"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Shades</a
          >, FuryStack&rsquo;s own JSX-based UI library. It is bundled with
          <a href="https://vite.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Vite</a>
          and includes:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>A basic layout with header, body, and routing</li>
          <li>Login / logout using <code>@furystack/auth-jwt</code></li>
          <li>Type-safe API calls via <code>@furystack/rest-client-fetch</code></li>
          <li>Theming with <code>@furystack/shades-common-components</code></li>
        </ul>

        <hr />

        <h2>Tooling</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Linting:</strong> ESLint with <code>@furystack/eslint-plugin</code> + Prettier
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Unit tests:</strong>
            <a href="https://vitest.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Vitest</a> &mdash;
            run with <code>yarn test</code>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>E2E tests:</strong>
            <a href="https://playwright.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Playwright</a
            > &mdash; run with <code>yarn test:e2e</code>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Seed data:</strong>
            <code>yarn seed</code> creates a test user for development
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Git hooks:</strong> Husky + lint-staged for pre-commit linting and formatting
          </li>
        </ul>

        <hr />

        <h2>What&rsquo;s next?</h2>
        <p>
          Now that your project is running, explore the codebase and start adding your own models,
          endpoints, and pages. For deeper understanding of individual packages, check out the
          <a href="/getting-started/">Getting Started hub</a> for guided learning paths.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-main {
    flex-grow: 1;
    padding: calc(64px + 48px) 5vw 80px;
    background: #fff;
  }
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    .page-main {
      background: var(--color-darkmode);
    }
  }

  .page-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    color: var(--color-midgrey);
  }
  .breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .page-inner h1 {
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    font-size: 3.6rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .page-inner h1 {
      font-size: 2.6rem;
    }
  }

  .page-content {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-body);
  }
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    .page-content {
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72);
    }
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 2.1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-darkgrey);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    .lead {
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
    }
  }

  .page-content h2 {
    margin-top: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .page-content h3 {
    margin-top: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .page-content pre {
    margin: 16px 0 24px;
    background: var(--color-darkgrey);
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
  }
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    .page-content pre {
      background: var(--color-darkmode-l04);
    }
  }

  .page-content ol,
  .page-content ul {
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .page-content li {
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .page-content li pre {
    margin-top: 8px;
  }
</style>
